# ---> Go
# If you prefer the allow list template instead of the deny list, see community template:
# https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/community/Golang/Go.AllowList.gitignore
#
# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib
# goreleaser's output. Leading slash anchors to repo root so it doesn't
# accidentally swallow web/dist/ (the Svelte build output, which has
# its own .gitignore policy in web/.gitignore).
/dist/
# Built binary at the repo root; leading slash anchors to root so the
# cmd/diesel/ source directory isn't excluded.
/diesel

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Output of the go coverage tool, specifically when used with LiteIDE
*.out
coverage.html

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
vendor/

# Go workspace file
go.work
go.work.sum

# env file
.env

# ---> Qt
# C++ objects and libs
*.slo
*.lo
*.o
*.a
*.la
*.lai
*.so
*.so.*
*.dll
*.dylib

# Qt-es
object_script.*.Release
object_script.*.Debug
*_plugin_import.cpp
/.qmake.cache
/.qmake.stash
*.pro.user
*.pro.user.*
*.qbs.user
*.qbs.user.*
*.moc
moc_*.cpp
moc_*.h
qrc_*.cpp
ui_*.h
*.qmlc
*.jsc
Makefile*
*build-*
*.qm
*.prl

# Qt unit tests
target_wrapper.*

# QtCreator
*.autosave

# QtCreator Qml
*.qmlproject.user
*.qmlproject.user.*

# QtCreator CMake
CMakeLists.txt.user*

# QtCreator 4.8< compilation database
compile_commands.json

# QtCreator local machine specific files for imported projects
*creator.user*

*_qmlcache.qrc

